<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-396-888  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 396 888.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  June 26 1989 v6 n25 p21(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T revamps object-oriented language system. (C++ Language System2.0) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Product:   C++ Language System 2.0 (Program development software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Object-Oriented LanguagesEnhancementsProduct IntroductionProgramming Languages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ATandamp;T Revamps Object-Oriented Language SystemandM;GREENSBORO, N.C.andP;  -- ATandamp;T has announced C++ Language System 2.0, a newversion of the company's object-oriented programming language.andM;Although object orientation has become an industry buzzword and C++ has beentripping off many tongues, ATandamp;T's language itself had yet to be properlydocumented and supported, ATandamp;T officials said.andM;C++ version 2.0 offers more effective documentation and support than theprevious version, so users can design applications more easily.andP;  ATandamp;T isproviding a number of new features with the new version.andM;Multiple inheritance allows a child object to inherit the properties of morethan one parent.andM;&quot;In a windows environment, for example, a developer can define generic,different windows that are scrollable and sizable, say--and then new windowscan be created from those windows, incorporating those features withouthaving to add extra code,&quot; said Paul Fill-inich, ATandamp;T's product manager forC++.andP;  &quot;When you're dealing with graphics and complex code, being able toreuse code through multiple inheritance really makes things more efficient.&quot;andM;Other new features of this release include type-safe linkage, defaultmemberwise assignment and initialization of classes, overloaded to operatorcapabilities, and the ability of each class to define its own &quot;new&quot; and&quot;delete&quot; operators, officials said.andM;The C++ Language System 2.0 is available now.andP;  It is priced at $20,000 forthe first CPU and $5,000 for each additional CPU.andM;ATandamp;T Information Systems can be contacted at P.O. Box 25000, Greensboro, NC27420, (800) 828-8649.andO;</TEXT></DOC>